<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Shell irregularly subtriangular, medium thickness, and quite inflated. Anterior margin regularly rounded; ventral margin nearly straight; posterior margin obliquely arc-shaped. Umbo prominent and slightly eroded. Umbo sculptured with feebly wavy wrinkles. Posterior slope formed by the ventral margin and posterior margin low, triangular. Epidermis shining black or with brownish-yellow hue. Only one cardinal tooth in each valve, shape triangular. Laterals thick, a little curved, 2 in each valve. Nacre reddish-bronze in colour.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Length 43-52 mm, height 29-36 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">The specific epithet is derived from the type locality, Rentian Town.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
